{{- /*
  gateways/tyk/_shared/templates/p11_response_rewrite.tmpl

  Tyk Classic body-transform template shared by tyk/p11-resp-body and
  tyk/p12-full-pipeline. Tyk's `transform_response` middleware uses the
  Go text/template engine plus the bundled Sprig v3 FuncMap. The
  canonical resp-body contract is:

      * inject  $.bench.injected = true
      * drop    $.origin

  Sprig provides exactly two helpers we need to do this without any
  ad-hoc string surgery on the upstream JSON:

      * `unset DICT KEY`     - delete KEY from DICT, return the dict
      * `set DICT KEY VALUE` - set KEY in DICT to VALUE, return the dict
      * `dict K1 V1 K2 V2 …` - construct a literal map[string]any
      * `mustToJson VALUE`   - JSON-marshal VALUE, error out on failure

  Both `unset` and `set` mutate their first argument in place AND return
  the (now-mutated) dict; we pin the return to `$_` so it is not
  rendered into the output stream. After the two mutations, we
  serialise the entire (still-the-same) `.` map back to JSON and emit
  it as the new response body. Tyk takes the rendered bytes, replaces
  the upstream body, and recomputes Content-Length on the way out.

  The template is `input_type: "json"` so `.` is `map[string]interface{}`
  decoded by `encoding/json` from the upstream body. Non-object
  upstream responses (HTML, binary) would fail this template — the
  fixture probes only hit go-httpbin's `/anything` which always
  returns a JSON object, so this is the right shape for the bench.
*/ -}}
{{- $_ := unset . "origin" -}}
{{- $_ := set   . "bench" (dict "injected" true) -}}
{{- mustToJson . -}}
